2026-03-18 00:38:20 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Philip Morris International Inc earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/future', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Future Growth - Simply Wall St', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$295.5b\n\n# Philip Morris International Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\nPhilip Morris International is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 8.4% and 6.4% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 8.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 1315.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n8.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n8.66%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco earnings growth | 7.6% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.4% |\n| Future return on equity | 1,315.67% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 19 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026 [...] Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next\n\n### First quarter 2025 earnings released: EPS: US$1.72 (vs US$1.38 in 1Q 2024)\n\n### Now 23% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### What You Can Learn From Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) P/E\n\nWhat You Can Learn From Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) P/E\n\n### First quarter dividend of US$1.35 announced\n\n### Philip Morris International Declares Regular Quarterly Dividend, Payable on July 15, 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Forecast for Full Year 2025 [...] ### Philip Morris International Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Urges U.S. Food and Drug Administration Advisory Committee to Recommend Continued Marketing of IQOS as Modified Risk Product\n\n### Now 21% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Second quarter dividend increased to US$1.47\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc Declares Regular Quarterly Dividend, Payable on October 20, 2025\n\n### Now 20% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Now 20% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next", 'score': 0.9999076, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.gurufocus.com/news/8626580/philip-morris-pm-reaffirms-2026-earnings-forecast', 'title': 'Philip Morris (PM) Reaffirms 2026 Earnings Forecast - GuruFocus', 'content': "Philip Morris International operates within the Consumer Defensive sector, specifically in the Tobacco Products industry. The company boasts a substantial market capitalization of $285.88 billion, reflecting its significant influence and stability within the market.\n\n## Financial Health Analysis\n\nPhilip Morris International has demonstrated consistent revenue growth, with a 3-year revenue growth rate of 8.4%. The company's profitability is underscored by its impressive operating margin of 36.74% and a net margin of 27.92%. These figures highlight the company's ability to efficiently manage its operations and maintain a strong bottom line. [...] Philip Morris International (PM) is set to discuss its strategic outlook at the 2026 Consumer Analyst Group of New York Conference, scheduled for 10:00 a.m. ET. The company has reiterated its full-year 2026 earnings per share (EPS) projection, initially announced on February 6th, ranging from $7.87 to $8.02.\n\nWhen adjustments amounting to $0.51 per share are excluded, the adjusted diluted EPS is anticipated to be between $8.38 and $8.53. This forecasted range marks an expected increase of 11.1% to 13.1% compared to the $7.54 EPS reported in 2025. Furthermore, excluding the positive effect of currency fluctuations at current exchange rates, which is valued at $0.27 per share, the growth is projected to be within 7.5% to 9.5%. [...] Philip Morris International Inc, created from the international operations of Altria in 2008, is a leading player in the tobacco industry. The company sells cigarettes and reduced-risk products, including heat sticks, vapes, and oral nicotine offerings, primarily outside of the US. With the 2023 acquisition of Swedish Match, a leading manufacturer of traditional oral tobacco products and nicotine pouches primarily in the US and Scandinavia, PMI is not only dominant in smokable products but also has the Iqos and Zyn brands, which respectively dominate heated tobacco and nicotine pouches in most markets.", 'score': 0.99986017, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.marketscreener.com/quote/stock/PHILIP-MORRIS-INTERNATION-2836699/finances/', 'title': 'Philip Morris International, Inc.: Financial Data Forecasts Estimates ...', 'content': '### Cash Flow Forecast: Philip Morris International, Inc.\n\n| Fiscal Period: December | 2021 | 2022 | 2023 | 2024 | 2026 | 2027 | 2028 |\n ---  ---  ---  --- |\n| CAPEX 1 | 748 | 1,077 | 1,321 | 1,444 | 1,552 | 1,576 | 1,631 |\n| Change  43.98% | 22.66% | 9.31%  1.54% | 3.5% |\n| Free Cash Flow (FCF) 1 | 11,219 | 9,726 | 7,883 | 10,773 | 13,133 | 14,450 | 15,336 |\n| Change  -13.31% | -18.95% | 36.66%  10.03% | 6.13% |\n| Announcement Date | 2/10/22 | 2/9/23 | 2/8/24 | 2/6/25  - \n\n## Forecast Financial Ratios: Philip Morris International, Inc. [...] | Change  -4.89% | -10.18% | 16.74% | 13.78% | 13.3% | 9.83% | 9.79% |\n| Net income 1 | 9,109 | 9,048 | 7,813 | 7,057 | 11,348 | 12,405 | 13,566 | 14,780 |\n| Change  -0.67% | -13.65% | -9.68% | 60.8% | 9.31% | 